    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">574.D7/1647: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_HC4" type="from">Hsieh
                            Chieh-shih</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="25" xml:id="d220fn25">This telegram was filed without
                        acknowledgment.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Changchun</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-19">August 19,
                            1932</date>].<lb/>[Received August 19—10:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I had the honor in my telegram addressed to Your Excellency, dated April 23,<note
                        n="26" xml:id="d220fn26">
                        <ref target="frus1932v03#pg_719">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p.
                            719</ref>.</note> to express the desire of the Government of the State
                        <pb facs="0301" n="203" xml:id="pg_203"/> of Manchuria to adhere to the
                    International Radio Telegraphic Convention<note n="27" xml:id="d220fn27">Signed
                        at Washington, November 25, 1927, <ref target="frus1927v01#pg_288">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1927, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 288</ref>.</note> and to regulations
                    annexed thereto.</p>
                <p>I now respectfully ask that you will be good enough to take prompt action in the
                    matter requested in the said telegraphic communication.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_HC4">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hsieh Chieh-shih</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
